  "texts": [
    "Older versions of the metadata are preserved so a client can choose to request older data for compatibility or other reasons.• <VER>/schemas/ A prefix containing the version-specific JSON schemas for all objects in the data model.",
    "• <VER>/config.json Returns a configuration object containing base URL prefixes and other metadata necessary for programmatic use of the following API.",
    "Follows the JSON schema defined by DataConfig.json.",
    "• <VER>/DATA_NOTES.md Returns a Markdown document containing the data release notes.",
    "• <VER>/metadata/by_body/<body_id>.json For a given body ID (i.e., the identifier for a specific EM neuron reconstruction), returns metadata such as a path to a representative image, neuron names, etc."
  ],
